dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100H is a hierarchical version of CIFAR-100, which organizes the 100 classes into 20 coarse categories, allowing for hierarchical classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100H
